snippet.textDisplay:
I've listened to the song for the first time and I said to myself : "cute guy eventhough I don't like his beard nor his movements but a wonderful voice... and daaaaamn, where was this girl hiding?Her voice is a gem!"
Few hours laters, I activated the autoplay and fell on the song again, I said : "waouuuh, it's really a hell of a song but the cute guy's movements are still annoying... maybe I should avoid looking at him and just listen to him"... and so I did.

After the end of the song...I repeated it, " I activated the subtitles again and read the lyrics, I said : " hmm... interesting... let's see the comments!" +Boota Sialkoti gave an astonishing insight and here I was, listening to the song again.

some 10 or 20 views after , I'm addicted to the song, I'm enjoying Umair's singing despite his movements but he's sexy (not cute anymore) so it's okay as long as my eyes are pleased and I cried when I've heard the couplet sung by Quratulain because it reminded me of my mother (don't worry, she's still alive) and how much she loves me!

For those who are complaning about Umair, remember that he didn't sing a lot in "charkha nolakha" eventhough his voice was matchless and I'd have rather listen to him without Atif's voice. I'm also sure that Quratulain will get another song where she'll be the leading singer. :-)

Excellently put together. Composition, melody, vocals, Umair and QB if any one element is missing or taken away we won't be talking and commenting on this song. Even the energy Umair has brought into this song by vocal and posture is outstanding. No one has done less than anyone on this stage. Lovely song and I keep listening to it. How many songs now days do you put on repeat? But this one! Love all the comments from India and the people who spread love with music.

Thank you QB and Umair and the team.
